reviewText: An excellent collection of increasingly hard to find films.  The Opening of Misty Beethoven is almost worth the price of the entire set.

Henry Paris (his fake name) directed these films, and I'm not surprised he used a phony name. It's insulting to have to watch porn stars like Jamie Gillis in every film, receiving oral sex, with a token licking for the females. These women are beautiful, and I'm sure they were properly auditioned, but it's well known they didn't get paid much to do a scene. Porn is supposed to arouse you, but it's been said the Song of Solomon in the Old Testament would make a porn star blush. Too much fellatio is like eating too much chocolate -- it'll make you sick. The situations in these films is so dumb (fellatio in a restaurant etc.) that it's pointless. Pamela Mann isn't bad, probably the best of the bunch. The video quality is pretty good.  They have some historical value, but that's about it. One caveat for men -- don't think you can walk up to any woman and have her drop to her knees for you. This only works in porn.

Back in the 70's it was the beginning of the sexual revolution.  Somehow it slowly changed and the porn pictures now are more interesting and uninhibited. I didn't really get interested in the old hummer and only gave it two starts.
Well presented and enjoyable look at how adult entertainment can be made. The actors actually looked like they enjoyed themselves.
